The paper deals with the mathematical properties of value functions in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves the study of geometric and topological properties, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of visualizations to enhance understanding suggests a connection to systems and control theory (cs.SY), while the mathematical analysis of the value function polytope relates to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
